[SN]TITLE[SN]
Cameroon's Aurelien Chedjou joins Turkish giants Galatasaray

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Cameroon defender Aurelien Chedjou has joined Turkish champions Galatasaray on a four-year deal.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
He signs from French club Lille for a fee of US$8.2m.
The 27-year-old is set play alongside his compatriot Dany Nounkeu in defence at Galatasaray, the duo are currently training with the national side ahead of a friendly against Ukraine on Sunday.
Chedjou played 154 Ligue 1 games for Lille after joining from FC Rouen in 2007, helping the northern club clinch the French title two years ago.
